.TH "drm_crtc_create_scaling_filter_property" 9 "drm_crtc_create_scaling_filter_property" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_crtc_create_scaling_filter_property \- create a new scaling filter property
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_crtc_create_scaling_filter_property
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ","
.BI "unsigned int supported_filters "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
drm CRTC
.IP "supported_filters" 12
bitmask of supported scaling filters, must include
BIT(DRM_SCALING_FILTER_DEFAULT).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function lets driver to enable the scaling filter property on a given
CRTC.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero for success or -errno
